<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-15T11:56:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-15T11:56:00-05:00" n="1473" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1473">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.48/15</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-15T11:00:00-05:56">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram of June 13, 6 p.m. Salvadorean Red Cross has accepted with
                            appropriate expression of appreciation 5,000 dollars; through an
                            amicable arrangement with Government’s commissions, Red Cross will
                            administer funds it accepts with free hand. Even so, more money for the
                            Red Cross and supplementary fund are necessary.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>